flowRoot.flowPara: Instructables Restaurant is the first open source restaurant in the world. Everything you see, use and eat is downloaded from instructables.com. It is therefore the first example of Open Interior Design and a good showcase of the possibilities offered by the Instructables platform.

Instructables is a web-based documentation platform where passionate people share what they do and how they do it, and learn from and collaborate with others. The seeds of Instructables germinated at the MIT Media Lab as the future founders of Squid Labs built places to share their projects and help others. Instructables supports the use of Creative Commons Licenses for uploaded instructables, becoming therefore one of the first big platforms and communities of Open Design. Recently it has been acquired by Autodesk recently, showing that Open Design is now the focus of big companies.
